  "texts": [
    "These models represent the forefront of AI technology, with potential applications in spam detection that could surpass traditional and earlier machine learning approaches in both accuracy and efficiency.The objective of this comparative analysis is to evaluate the performance of unmodified ChatGPT-4 and Google Gemini in identifying spam within the SpamAssassin public mail corpus.",
    "By leveraging this well-established dataset, the study aims to provide a rigorous and fair comparison of these two AI models, focusing on their effectiveness in spam detection.",
    "This analysis is significant not only for advancing the academic understanding of AI capabilities in cybersecurity but also for guiding practical applications and development of more effective spam filtering tools.",
    "Through this research, we aim to highlight the strengths and limitations of each model, providing insights that could inform future improvements and innovations in the field of spam detection.A list of major contributions of this study are: 1) We conducted a comprehensive comparative analysis of ChatGPT-4 and Google Gemini's capabilities in spam detection using the SpamAssassin public mail corpus, providing a detailed evaluation of their performance based on standard metrics such as accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score.",
    "2) We illuminated the distinct characteristics and strengths of each AI model in the context of spam detection, with ChatGPT-4 exhibiting a balanced approach between precision and recall, and Google Gemini demonstrating a high recall rate, indicating its strength in identifying a broader array of spam emails."
